      "content": "therapists just try to fix you so you can go back to being \"normal\" for everyone else. it doesn't actually solve the feeling that there's nothing for me here. it just feels like i'm stuck in this loop of trying to exist in a world that wasn't built for me. sometimes i wonder if the only way to actually stop the exhaustion is to just... stop. to just find some kind of peace where i don't have to perform anymore.",
